I'm not very sure about that. If i understand correctly `fastAtomicAdd` API, numel argument (3rd arg) is the boundary for provided index (2nd arg). As provious code was using `grad_input_offset` which is `grad_input` plus an offset (`((roi_batch_ind * channels + c) * height * width)`), we have to recompute the boundary for given index.

Maybe, we can use `grad_input` pointer and put the offset into index argument, so that numel will be `memory_span`:
```
auto offset = ((roi_batch_ind * channels + c) * height * width);
at::native::fastAtomicAdd(grad_input, offset + argmax, memory_span, ...);
```

